  gather(key='variable',value='value','work_type','smoking_status','Residence_type','hypertension','heart_disease','gender','ever_married') %>%

#1-6
x1<-xtabs(formula=~stroke+gender,data=data)
X1<-chisq.test(x1)
x2<-xtabs(formula=~stroke+hypertension,data=data)
X2<-chisq.test(x2)
x3<-xtabs(formula=~stroke+heart_disease,data=data)
X3<-chisq.test(x3)
x4<-xtabs(formula=~stroke+ever_married,data=data)
X4<-chisq.test(x4)
x5<-xtabs(formula=~stroke+work_type,data=data)
X5<-chisq.test(x5)
x6<-xtabs(formula=~stroke+Residence_type,data=data)
X6<-chisq.test(x6)
x7<-xtabs(formula=~stroke+smoking_status,data=data)
X7<-chisq.test(x7)
x_set<-c(X1$p.value,X2$p.value,X3$p.value,X4$p.value,X5$p.value,X6$p.value,X7$p.value)
x_set<-ifelse(x_set<0.05,'denied','accept')
cate_Var<-c('gender','hypertension','heart_disease','ever_married','work_type','Residence_type','smoking_status')
chi<-x_set
df<-data.frame(cate_Var,chi)
df

#Chapter3
library(factoextra)
## Welcome! Want to learn more? See two factoextra-related books at https://goo.gl/ve3WBa
library(cluster)

#3-1
data1<-data[,c(1,6,7)]
data1<-scale(data1)

#3-2
fviz_nbclust(data1, kmeans, method = "wss")

fviz_nbclust(data1, kmeans, method = "silhouette")

#적절한 k=3,4(y값이 제일 높을 때)

#3-3
set.seed(1234)
cl<-kmeans(data1,3,nstart=1,iter.max = 30)
fviz_cluster(cl, data = data1, stand=F)

#3-4
cf<-select(data,where(is.numeric))
cf<-mutate(cf,cluster=cl$cluster)
cf1<-cf %>% ggplot(aes(x=factor(cluster),y=age))+
  geom_boxplot(outlier.shape=NA,alpha=0.5,fill=c('#845ec2', '#ffc75f', '#ff5e78'),color=c('#845ec2', '#ffc75f', '#ff5e78'))+
  stat_boxplot(geom='errorbar',color=c('#845ec2', '#ffc75f', '#ff5e78'))+
  labs(x='cluster')+
  theme_bw()
cf2<-cf %>% ggplot(aes(x=factor(cluster),y=avg_glucose_level))+
  geom_boxplot(outlier.shape=NA,alpha=0.5,fill=c('#845ec2', '#ffc75f', '#ff5e78'),color=c('#845ec2', '#ffc75f', '#ff5e78'))+
  stat_boxplot(geom='errorbar',color=c('#845ec2', '#ffc75f', '#ff5e78'))+
  labs(x='cluster')+
  theme_bw()
cf3<-cf %>% ggplot(aes(x=factor(cluster),y=bmi))+
  geom_boxplot(outlier.shape=NA,alpha=0.5,fill=c('#845ec2', '#ffc75f', '#ff5e78'),color=c('#845ec2', '#ffc75f', '#ff5e78'))+
  stat_boxplot(geom='errorbar',color=c('#845ec2', '#ffc75f', '#ff5e78'))+
  labs(x='cluster')+
  theme_bw()
grid.arrange(cf1,cf2,cf3,ncol=3)
